"Here is the motivation thread designed to weave through your academic paper:\n\n**CORE_NARRATIVE:** \nCurrent light field depth estimation fails on ubiquitous non-Lambertian materials because data-driven models are fundamentally \"blind\" to specular and scattering reflections, resulting in severe texture copying and depth blurring. To cure this blindness, we introduce a physically interpretable framework that decodes light-material interactions via an MRI-like angular frequency analysis and a physical dual-mask model. By embedding these explicit physical priors into a material-aware deep fusion architecture, we resolve the breakdown of viewpoint consistency and restore reliable 3D perception in complex, real-world environments.\n\n**INTRO_HOOK:** \nOpen by highlighting the ubiquity of non-Lambertian materials (glass, metal) in the real world and the catastrophic failure of modern 3D vision systems in these scenarios due to an over-reliance on heuristic cues and purely data-driven features. Frame the central thesis immediately: achieving robust depth estimation requires moving beyond pattern recognition to explicitly decode the physics of light-material interactions.\n\n**GAP_BRIDGE:** \nTransition from related work by stating that while prior methods attempt to mask out non-Lambertian regions or use robust loss functions, they still fundamentally ignore the underlying physical reflection types, relying instead on broken viewpoint consistency assumptions. Bridge this gap by proposing a paradigm shift: formulating depth estimation as a physical reverse-engineering problem that explicitly maps angular light-field samples to distinct material properties.\n\n**METHOD_JUSTIFY:** \nState that every architectural choice is driven by physical optics, beginning with the MRI-like 2D-DFT on 81 angular samples to map Lambertian, specular, and scattering reflections into distinct low, high, and mid-frequency k-space signatures. Justify the MACVO-Net and dual-mask design by explaining that once a pixel's physical reflection type is classified, the network can leverage cost-volume flatness as a natural uncertainty signal, allowing the material-aware fusion module to intelligently weight geometric cues rather than blindly trusting broken EPI consistency.\n\n**EXPERIMENT_VALIDATE:** \nStructure the experiments to directly prove that physical interpretability cures \"blindness,\" demonstrating quantitatively (e.g., the 85%+ material classification accuracy and massive contrast improvements) that specular/scattering regions are actively decoded rather than smoothed over. Emphasize qualitative and quantitative reductions in \"texture copying\" and \"depth blurring\" on complex reflective scenes compared to state-of-the-art baselines, proving superior generalization to uncontrolled environments.\n\n**CONCLUSION_ECHO:** \nConclude by reiterating that embedding explicit physical dual-masking and k-space frequency analysis successfully cures the fundamental \"blindness\" of deep networks to non-Lambertian physics. End with a forward-looking statement: that anchoring data-driven models in Maxwell-equation-based physical priors is the critical pathway to deploying reliable 3D vision systems in highly complex, uncontrolled real-world settings."